menu "ESP BMS LVGL Bridge"

    config ESP_BMS_LVGL_BRIDGE_SPI_DRAW_BUFFER_HEIGHT
        int "SPI draw buffer height"
        range 10 120
        default 64
        help
            Draw buffer height in display rows for the ESP LVGL adapter SPI
            display path. Larger values reduce visible row-band refresh during
            whole-page drags, but consume more internal DMA-capable RAM.

            At 320 px wide and RGB565, 64 rows use about 40 KiB for the single
            partial-mode draw buffer. Keep this below a full frame on ESP32
            without PSRAM.

    config ESP_BMS_LVGL_BRIDGE_TASK_MAX_DELAY_MS
        int "LVGL adapter task max delay"
        range 1 15
        default 5
        help
            Maximum sleep interval for the ESP LVGL adapter worker task in
            milliseconds. Lower values improve touch-following latency at the
            cost of more frequent LVGL work.

    config ESP_BMS_LVGL_BRIDGE_DOUBLE_BUFFER
        bool "Use two LVGL SPI draw buffers"
        default n
        help
            Allocate a secondary SPI draw buffer for the ESP LVGL adapter
            partial render mode. This can improve overlap between rendering and
            SPI flush work during page drags, but at 320 px wide and 64 rows it
            costs another about 40 KiB of internal DMA-capable RAM.

            Keep this disabled in the normal image until hardware logs confirm
            enough free internal RAM remains after LVGL, Wi-Fi, and HTTP start.

endmenu
